Novak Djokovic isn't surprised he keeps winning Grand Slam titles. We shouldn't be, either

Novak Djokovic, at age 36, continues to dominate men's tennis and has reclaimed the No. 1 spot in the ATP rankings. With his victory at the U.S. Open, Djokovic now has 24 major championships, tying Margaret Court for the most in tennis history. He has won three Grand Slam titles this season and remains unfazed by the younger generation of players.
